OL,3,CGovernment announces support for
OL,4,Cpollack fishers affected by zero-catch
OL,5,Climit
OL,7,FDefra has also announced a new
OL,8,Fscientific study that will see
OL,9,Fscientists and fishermen work to
OL,10,Fincrease their understanding of
OL,11,Fpollack stock in the region.
OL,13,FFishermen will be paid for their
OL,14,Ftraining and for taking part in the
OL,15,Fstudy, according to Defra, and can
OL,16,Fsell any pollack they catch.
OL,18,FIt comes after increased pressure on
OL,19,Fthe government by local MPs, including
OL,20,Fthe Conservative for South East
OL,21,FCornwall, Sheryll Murray.
